<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local pointer 'record' is declared as a non-const OS_common_record_t * but is only used for read-only access (reading record->name_entry and passing it to memcpy). Per MISRA C 2023 R8.13 it should be const-qualified (e.g. const OS_common_record_t *record). This change is feasible because assigning the non-const return of OS_ObjectIdGlobalFromToken to a const pointer is allowed. Therefore the current declaration violates R8.13.
</scenario>
